    "body": ">  think the different order and missing production types show that the initial implementation isn't as flexible as it should be to suit all mods.\n\nI think that's being a bit too polite - our hotkey implementation is inflexible and a bit crap in general.  We are well past the point where hardcoded hotkey types no longer work well.\n\nWe are going to need to move towards a system where ButtonWidgets can bind to named hotkey types that are defined in an external yaml file and customized per-mod in settings.yaml, but we've known this for a long time now.\n"
